Walker: Communities in Senate District 31 receive more than $4 million in road-funding grant

STATEHOUSE (April 10, 2024) — Communities in Senate District 31 will receive more than $4 million to improve roads and bridges through the Community Crossings Matching Grant Program (CCMG), said State Sen. Kyle Walker (R-Lawrence). more »

WALKER WELCOMES LAWRENCE CENTRAL HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS BASKETBALL TEAM TO THE STATEHOUSE

WALKER WELCOMES LAWRENCE CENTRAL HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS BASKETBALL TEAM TO THE STATEHOUSE: State Sen. Kyle Walker (R-Lawrence) presents Senate Concurrent Resolution 25 Monday, March 4 to recognize the Lawrence Central High School girls basketball team for their Indiana High School Athletic Association (IHSAA) 4A state championship win. Lawrence Central High School won the 4A state title with a score of 55-28. The Bears held their competitors to the fewest points ever by a team in an IHSAA 4A state championship game. more »

Walker Presents Five-Term Lawrence Clerk Sagamore of the Wabash Award

LAWRENCE (Feb. 6, 2024) — State Sen. Kyle Walker (R-Lawrence), on behalf of Gov. Eric Holcomb, presented former Lawrence Clerk Kathy Walton with a Sagamore of the Wabash award for her 27 years of dedicated service to the City of Lawrence on Saturday, Feb. 3. more »
